<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 07 at 2:49PM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of Yadkin County
through 315 PM EDT...
At 249 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Shacktown, or near East Bend, moving southeast at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Yadkinville...
Boonville...
East Bend...
Nebo...
Courtney...
Huntsville...
and Shacktown.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>Seek shelter inside a building.</instruction>
